DeoDap MCP Dashboard — Project Guide
A courier-billing dashboard for DeoDap. React + Vite frontend, FastAPI backend, with live data pulled from the Ship MCP server (and a mock fallback wherever no live source exists).

1. The one architectural rule
The frontend never imports data directly. Every page gets data through:


React page → TanStack Query hook (src/services/*) → Axios → /api/... → FastAPI router → service layer → Ship MCP (live)  ─or─  mock JSON (fallback)
TypeScript types are generated from FastAPI's OpenAPI schema. If you change a backend response shape, you regenerate types — you never hand-write them.

